Package physicalLayer

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Agent
    An abstract class to model an Agent that is situated in an environment, that has a two-layered neural network architecture for learning and decision-making.
    Cell
    A class to model a position in the 2D environment.
    CellObject
    An abstract class to model an object that is contained in a Cell.
    Location
    A class to model a location in a 2D environment.
    PhysicalLayer
    A class to model a 2D grid-world environment with different objects placed in it.
    Resource
    A class to model a Resource object, which has a location.
    SocialActionAgent
    An implementation of the Agent abstract class capable of social action, where social action is operationalised as: goal-rational action, where the action taken is considered to be the most likely to achieve a goal; traditional action, where the action taken is comparable to the representative state of the population at the current timestep; random action, where the action taken is completely random. A SocialActionAgent is situated in an environment, that has a two-layered neural network architecture for learning and decision-making.
    Stone
    A class to model a non-dangerous Stone object, which can be picked up and used to build bridges in Water.
    Trap
    A class to model a dangerous Trap object.
    Water
    A class to model a dangerous Water object, which has a depth.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ActionType
    A class to model the different types of social action that an agent can employ in the River Crossing Dilemma.
